# CSRF where token is not tied to user session

## Vulnerability Type
CSRF	

## Difficulty
practitioner

## Platform
PortSwigger Web Security Academy

## Goal
This lab's email change functionality is vulnerable to CSRF. It uses tokens to try to prevent CSRF attacks, but they aren't integrated into the site's session handling system

## Root Cause
This lab's email change functionality is vulnerable to CSRF because the CSRF token is not tied to the user session, allowing token reuse across sessions.

## Exploitation Steps
1. Browse the application  
2. login with provided credentials  
3. intercept email change request  
4. in repeater tab observe CSRF token  
5. login to another account in private tab and copy CSRF token  
6. swap/reuse the token in the original session request  
7. go to engagement tools and generate CSRF PoC  
8. go to exploit server then deliver to victim  

## Impact
An attacker can change user email address  

